  "output": "Full picture now. No frontend exists yet (SvelteKit not built), no DB layer (no SQL queries). Analysis confined to `core/`.\n\n---\n\n## Performance Analysis\n\n### 1. N+1 Query Patterns ŌĆö Not yet applicable\n\nNo DB layer exists. But flag this **before** adding PostgreSQL:\n\n- `get_visible_state` (game_engine.py:83) called per-player per broadcast. When `GameState` comes from DB, naive load = 1 query per player per round. Use eager-join on `PlayerState` + `IncomingShipment` rows up front.\n- `is_round_complete` (game.py:56) rebuilds `active_roles` set on every call ŌĆö will hurt once this triggers a DB filter.\n\n---\n\n### 2. React Re-renders ŌĆö N/A\n\nNo React. SvelteKit not implemented yet. Nothing to audit.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Caching Opportunities\n\n**a) `incoming_orders` computed but never read**\n\n`PlayerState.incoming_orders` (game.py:37) gets appended every round in `place_orders` (order_processor.py:72) but is **never read anywhere**. Dead accumulation. Drop it or wire it to actual logic.\n\n**b) `active_roles` rebuilt every `is_round_complete` call**\n\ngame.py:56:\n```python\n# Current ŌĆö rebuilds set on every WebSocket tick\ndef is_round_complete(self) -> bool:\n    active_roles = {role for role, ps in self.players.items() if not ps.is_ai}\n    return active_roles.issubset(self.orders_this_round.keys())\n```\n\nCache on game creation:\n```python\nclass GameState(BaseModel):\n    ...\n    _active_roles: set[PlayerRole] = Field(default_factory=set, exclude=True)\n\n    def model_post_init(self, _):\n        self._active_roles = {r for r, ps in self.players.items() if not ps.is_ai}\n\n    def is_round_complete(self) -> bool:\n        return self._active_roles.issubset(self.orders_this_round.keys())\n```\n\n**c) `pipeline` sum in `OrderUpToAI`**\n\nrule_based.py:16 ŌĆö recomputed on every AI tick even mid-round:\n```python\npipeline = sum(s.quantity for s in ps.incoming_shipments)\n```\nAdd computed property to `PlayerState`:\n```python\n@property\ndef pipeline_stock(self) -> int:\n    return sum(s.quantity for s in self.incoming_shipments)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Memory Leaks / Unbounded Growth\n\n**`incoming_orders` never drained** ŌĆö real issue\n\norder_processor.py:72:\n```python\nupstream_ps.incoming_orders.append(order_qty)\n```\n\nNothing ever reads or clears this list. Over 26 rounds ├Ś 3 upstream players = 26 entries per player accumulating silently. Either remove the field or consume it in `fulfill_orders`:\n\n```python\n# In fulfill_orders, for upstream demand, read from incoming_orders\ndemand_by_role[role] = upstream_ps.incoming_orders.pop(0) if upstream_ps.incoming_orders else 0\n```\n\nCurrently `fulfill_orders` reads `state.orders_this_round` directly instead, making `incoming_orders` fully redundant.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Redundant Computations\n\n**a) Double iteration of `incoming_shipments`** ŌĆö highest-frequency hot path\n\norder_processor.py:7ŌĆō13 iterates the list twice per player per round:\n```python\n# Current ŌĆö two passes\narrived = sum(s.quantity for s in ps.incoming_shipments if s.arrives_in_rounds == 1)\nps.incoming_shipments = [\n    IncomingShipment(quantity=s.quantity, arrives_in_rounds=s.arrives_in_rounds - 1)\n    for s in ps.incoming_shipments\n    if s.arrives_in_rounds > 1\n]\n```\n\nSingle-pass fix:\n```python\narrived = 0\nnext_shipments: list[IncomingShipment] = []\nfor s in ps.incoming_shipments:\n    if s.arrives_in_rounds == 1:\n        arrived += s.quantity\n    else:\n        next_shipments.append(\n            IncomingShipment(quantity=s.quantity, arrives_in_rounds=s.arrives_in_rounds - 1)\n        )\nps.inventory += arrived\nps.incoming_shipments = next_shipments\n```\n\n**b) Import inside a loop** ŌĆö game_engine.py:32\n\n```python\nfor role in ROLE_ORDER:\n    from core.models import IncomingShipment  # ŌåÉ executed every iteration\n```\n\nMove to top of file. Python caches the module import but still does a `sys.modules` dict lookup on every iteration of the loop.\n\n**c) Pydantic validation overhead on shipment decrement**\n\nEach `IncomingShipment(quantity=..., arrives_in_rounds=...)` in the list comprehension triggers full Pydantic v2 validation per shipment per player per round. For the inner simulation loop, consider:\n\n```python\nclass IncomingShipment(BaseModel):\n    model_config = ConfigDict(frozen=False)\n    ...\n```\n\nThen mutate `s.arrives_in_rounds -= 1` in place instead of reconstructing. No new object allocation, no re-validation.\n\n---\n\n### Priority order\n\n| # | Issue | File | Impact |\n|---|-------|------|--------|\n| 1 | `incoming_orders` never consumed ŌĆö dead growth | order_processor.py:72, game.py:37 | Memory + logic bug |\n| 2 | Double iteration of `incoming_shipments` | order_processor.py:7ŌĆō13 | CPU, called every round per player |\n| 3 | Import inside loop | game_engine.py:32 | Minor but trivial fix |\n| 4 | `active_roles` set rebuilt per tick | game.py:56 | Cache miss cost at WebSocket scale |\n| 5 | Pydantic reconstruction on shipment decrement | order_processor.py:12 | GC pressure at scale |\n\nNo frontend, no DB yet ŌĆö the `incoming_orders` issue is both a correctness concern and the only real unbounded growth pattern. Fix that first.\n",
